parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Rotor Warping and Excessive Wear
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Warped brake rotors can cause the vehicle to vibrate or shake while driving, leading to loss of control, and increased stopping distances, which can result in accidents.
symptoms: difficulty controlling the vehicle while turning or changing lanes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Abnormal brake noise and vibration can indicate a problem with the brake system, which can lead to reduced braking performance and increased stopping distances, potentially causing accidents.
Failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose braking ability, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: vehicle goes backward and jerks forward while sitting in traffic

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the Anti-lock Braking System (ABS) can cause the vehicle to lose traction and stability, leading to accidents or loss of control.
The failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, compromising the safety of vehicle occupants.
Unintended airbag deployment can cause injuries, distractions, and loss of vehicle control, increasing the risk of accidents.
Airbag system malfunctions can lead to false warnings, unintended deployments, or failure to deploy in the event of a crash, compromising vehicle safety.
The failure of the intake manifold can cause the engine to overheat, leading to a loss of power, and potentially resulting in a fire.
symptoms: flames coming from under the hood.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine oil leaks can cause the engine to overheat, leading to a loss of power, and potentially resulting in a fire.
symptoms: oil dripping onto the exhaust system

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the speed control deactivation switch can cause the vehicle to malfunction, leading to a loss of control and potentially resulting in an accident.
symptoms: Leaking fluid from the speed control deactivation switch.
